entry.title: Ukraine Says Missile Strike Kills 22 as Country Marked Subdued Independence Day
entry.content: President Volodymyr Zelensky said a Russian missile hit a passenger train in eastern Ukraine and killed at least 22 people, as the U.S. pledged a further $3 billion to support the Ukrainian military in the months ahead.

entry.title: Cuban Migrants Head to U.S. in Record Numbers
entry.content: Economic hardship and political repression have driven tens of thousands of Cubans to leave the Communist-led island nation.
